Best shaved ice ever... it was really soft compared to all the other ones I've tried. I got the lychee, mango, and melona with condensed milk and lilikoi cream on top.
Try the omakase. The only one I didn't like from the set was the ebi with the fermented shrimp paste on top. Get the red bean ice cream for dessert!
Good service and the food came out pretty quick. The ube pancakes were delicious. The dulce de leche waffles were a bit too dense for me but the flavor was good, not overly sweet.
Came here for the prawns but they were out. Their garlic butter shrimp was nowhere near comparable to mackys or even giovannis. Found a cooked pincher bug in our food.. they offered me a refund

Get the bbq shrimp plate, red beans & rice, and sweet tea. The buffalo poboy was ok but not great. Service was amazing for it being a food truck. They come out and offer to bring you sweet tea refills
The green tea, lilikoi, and guava flavors were all good. Add condensed milk and red beans! The line was super long but it moves by quick.
This place is way better than giovannis! Shrimps are juicier and the flavor wasn't bitter. Get the garlic butter with hot sauce on the side and the spicy hot plate.
The spicy ramen here was good, add in corn and an egg. Wish they had their eggs soft boiled style though.
Great service! The malasadas were all good. We got original, cinnamon sugar, and li hing. The malasada puffs were ok but I prefer it without the filling.
I got the combo with spicy ahi and the hawaiian ahi over brown rice. It was about 7 bucks for the combo and the fish was super fresh.

Food here is decent, they are mostly known for their desserts. Their banana lassi was good.

534 Vinh Khanh St., Wd. 8, Dist. 4 (Khánh Hội)

tip.text: It's the most popular spot down seafood street and it was packed when we went. They have burnt rice (really good) and a variety of shellfish as well as balut eggs and quail. They have outdoor seating.

tip.text: The French Toast ice cream tastes like a butterfingers bar, but it's so good! It's not too sweet and it has crunchy bits in it :)

tip.text: The seabass and scallop lunch plate was cooked perfectly. The desserts here were all soooo good! We had the chocolate fondant, tart with vanilla ice cream, and pistachio creme brulee.
Great place to relax and unwind for the day. They offer massages, facials, anti-aging treatments, coolsculpting, etc. They also have a pool and sauna. I got a 90 min foot massage and it felt great!
It's like pepper lunch where they serve your food as it cooks over a stone plate. The salmon with roe was pretty plain even with the garlic and honey sauces added; it needs terryaki sauce and spices.

tip.text: They have a huge variety of MMA and weight training equipment; they offer personal training- boxing, bjj, etc. The staff always keeps this place super clean! Restaurant & juice bar are opening soon :)
Loved it here. Great atmosphere, was packed during lunch time. The smoked salmon eggs on bread and salted caramel cupcake were really good. The sunrise drink was like a lukewarm smoothie though.
We had a set dinner menu for a birthday party. It came with oysters, a salad, scallops, a lobster bisque, and choice of entree. Everything tasted great. The setting was very ambient and romantic.

Great service and quality food. They have many varieties of food to choose from. The mango prawn salad in the lunch set is delicious. The seabass was good too but the wait between the 2 was a bit long
Love this place! Great spot to eat, drink beers, chill and watch some games. They have burgers, pizzas, salads, beers, pasta, etc. I love the fish cake sandwich on their panini bread :)
I've been here for both dimsum and dinner. Everything has been really good :) service is always fast even when it's busy.
Service is always great. They're always checking in on you. Risotto was hard. I recommend sticking to pizza here. The garlic mushroom pizza and the cheese salmon pizza are both thin and delicious.
